nwIpxMibRevText.name: nwIpxMibRevText
nwIpxMibRevText.description: Indicates the current revision level of the IPX MIB in textual format.

nwIpxSysRouterId.name: nwIpxSysRouterId
nwIpxSysRouterId.description: The IPX Address used to uniquely identify the host (device) running IPX Routing Services. The value of nwIpxSysRouterId is equal to the highest IPX address assigned in the IPX Address Table.

nwIpxSysAdminStatus.name: nwIpxSysAdminStatus
nwIpxSysAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of IPX Routing Services system-wide. Enabled (3) causes IPX Routing Services to become active on all router ports configured and enabled for IPX Routing Services. Disabled (2) causes IPX routing services to become inactive system-wide.

nwIpxSysOperStatus.name: nwIpxSysOperStatus
nwIpxSysOperStatus.description: Indicates the operating condition of IPX Routing Services system-wide. The value of nwIpxSysOperStatus indicates any problem with your IPX Routing Services configuration. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwIpxSysAdminStatus, IPX Routing Services is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwIpxSysAdminReset.name: nwIpxSysAdminReset
nwIpxSysAdminReset.description: Resets IPX Routing Services system-wide. Reset (2) forces a restart of IPX Routing Services without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports and without affecting any other routing services.

nwIpxSysOperationalTimel.name: nwIpxSysOperationalTimel
nwIpxSysOperationalTimel.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxSysOperStatus has been in its current administrative state.

nwIpxSysVersion.name: nwIpxSysVersion
nwIpxSysVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the IPX Routing Services firmware in textual format.

nwIpxFwdCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxFwdCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxFwdCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (system-wide) IPX packet and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxFwdCtrReset.name: nwIpxFwdCtrReset
nwIpxFwdCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate (system-wide) IPX packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the IPX aggregate counters to 0. nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxFwdCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxFwdCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrInPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrOutPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrFwdPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrFwdPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrFwdPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been forwarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrAddrErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrAddrErrPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrAddrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime, because of addressing errors in the IPX header.

nwIpxFwdCtrLenErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrLenErrPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrLenErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime, because an invalid packet length is contained in the IPX header.

nwIpxFwdCtrHdrErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHdrErrPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrHdrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime, because of an invalid IPX header.

nwIpxFwdCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrInBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrOutBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrFwdBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrFwdBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been forwarded, system-wide, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxFwd-CtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been discarded, system-wide during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostInPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostInPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrHostInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts
nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded by the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime, due to a lack of host resources.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostInBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostInBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been received by the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwIpxFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been discarded by the local host, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime due to a lack of host resources.

nwIpxFwdIfTable.name: nwIpxFwdIfTable
nwIpxFwdIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxFwdIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB2 ifIndex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfEntry.name: nwIpxFwdIfEntry
nwIpxFwdIfEntry.description: Each entry specifies the IPX Routing Services configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfIndex.name: nwIpxFwdIfIndex
nwIpxFwdIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfAdminStatus.name: nwIpxFwdIfAdminStatus
nwIpxFwdIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of IPX Routing Services on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes IPX Routing Services to become active. Disabled (2) causes it to become inactive.

nwIpxFwdIfOperStatus.name: nwIpxFwdIfOperStatus
nwIpxFwdIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of IPX Routing Services on the router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwIpxFwdIfOperStatus indicates any problem with the configuration of IPX Routing Services on the router port. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the state of nwIpxFwdIfAdminStatus IPX Routing Services is not operating because of an invalid port-level configuration.

nwIpxFwdIfOperationalTime.name: nwIpxFwdIfOperationalTime
nwIpxFwdIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxFwdIfOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwIpxFwdIfControl.name: nwIpxFwdIfControl
nwIpxFwdIfControl.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxFwdIfMtu.name: nwIpxFwdIfMtu
nwIpxFwdIfMtu.description: Specifies the Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) for IPX packets on the router port for which the entry exists. This includes the IPX header and data but does not include framing.

nwIpxFwdIfForwarding.name: nwIpxFwdIfForwarding
nwIpxFwdIfForwarding.description: Controls forwarding of IPX packets on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes IPX packets to be forwarded. Disabled (2) prevents IPX packets from being forwarded.

nwIpxFwdIfFrameType.name: nwIpxFwdIfFrameType
nwIpxFwdIfFrameType.description: Specifies the framing type for IPX packets forwarded on the router port for which the entry exists. Some frame types are valid for specific media types. The comments reflect those valid media types.

nwIpxFwdIfAclIdentifier.name: nwIpxFwdIfAclIdentifier
nwIpxFwdIfAclIdentifier.description: Specifies the Access Control ID of the Access Control List in effect for IPX packets being routed on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 indicates that no Access Control List is in effect.

nwIpxFwdIfAclStatus.name: nwIpxFwdIfAclStatus
nwIpxFwdIfAclStatus.description: Controls the operation of any Access Control List configured for IPX traffic on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) applies the Access Control List indicated by the value of nwIpxFwdIfAclIdentifier to all IPX traffic being routed to the port. Disabled (2) prevents the Access Control List from being applied.

nwIpxFwdIfCacheControl.name: nwIpxFwdIfCacheControl
nwIpxFwdIfCacheControl.description: Controls IPX Address caching on the router port for which the entry exists. When IPX Address caching is enabled, IPX Addresses used for address validation, filtering, and forwarding are stored in the cache. This cache is checked first before doing a full route table lookup, which speeds up the switching process. Enabled (3) turns on IPX Address caching. Disabled (2) turns it off.

nwIpxFwdIfCacheEntries.name: nwIpxFwdIfCacheEntries
nwIpxFwdIfCacheEntries.description: Indicates the number of entries in the IPX Address cache on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCacheHits.name: nwIpxFwdIfCacheHits
nwIpxFwdIfCacheHits.description: Indicates the number of times entries in the IPX Adddress cache have been used to provide the IPX Address required to validate, filter, or forward an IPX packet on the router port.

nwIpxFwdIfCacheMisses.name: nwIpxFwdIfCacheMisses
nwIpxFwdIfCacheMisses.description: Indicates the number of times the IPX Address required to validate, filter, or forward an IPX packet on the router port was not found in the IPX Address cache.

nwIpxAddressTable.name: nwIpxAddressTable
nwIpxAddressTable.description: This table contains an entry for each Novell network address assigned to each router port.

nwIpxAddrEntry.name: nwIpxAddrEntry
nwIpxAddrEntry.description: Each entry specifies the Novell network addressing information for the logical Novll network for which the entry exists.

nwIpxAddrIfIndex.name: nwIpxAddrIfIndex
nwIpxAddrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxAddrIfAddress.name: nwIpxAddrIfAddress
nwIpxAddrIfAddress.description: This is the Novell network number assigned to the logical Novell network for which the entry exists. The IpxAddress consists of a network number of 4 octets.

nwIpxAddrIfControl.name: nwIpxAddrIfControl
nwIpxAddrIfControl.description: Set this object to add or delete this entry from the table.

nwIpxAddrIfAddrType.name: nwIpxAddrIfAddrType
nwIpxAddrIfAddrType.description: Specifies whether the Novell network number, nwIpxAddrIfAddress, is the primary or secondary address for the router port.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrTable.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrTable
nwIpxFwdIfCtrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port configured and enabled for IPX Routing Services.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrEntry.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrEntry
nwIpxFwdIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates the current packet and byte count of IPX packets on the port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrIfIndex
nwIpxFwdIfCtrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxFwdIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the per-port IPX packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrReset.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrReset
nwIpxFwdIfCtrReset.description: Resets the per-port IPX packet and byte counters on the router port for which this entry exists. Reset (2) resets the counters to 0. nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxFwdIfCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrInPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been received, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationaltime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been forwarded, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded (dropped), during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded because of IPX addressing errors in the IPX header, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded because an invalid packet length was contained in the IPX header, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded because of an invalid IPX header, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrInBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been received, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been forwarded, during nwIpxFwdCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets administratively filtered, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been forwarded by the local host, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX packets that have been discarded by the local host, due to a lack of host resources, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwIpxFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX packets that have been discarded by the local host, due to a lack of host resources that were received, during nwIpxFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipAdminStatus.name: nwIpxRipAdminStatus
nwIpxRipAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX-RIP routing protocol system-wide. Enabled (3) causes IPX-RIP to become active on all router ports configured and enabled for IPX Routing Services. Disabled (2) causes IPX-RIP to become inactive.

nwIpxRipOperStatus.name: nwIpxRipOperStatus
nwIpxRipOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of IPX-RIP system-wide. The value of nwIpxRipOperStatus indicates any problem with your IPX-RIP configuration. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwIpxRipAdminStatus, IPX-RIP is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwIpxRipAdminReset.name: nwIpxRipAdminReset
nwIpxRipAdminReset.description: Resets the IPX-RIP routing protocol. Reset (2) forces a system-wide restart of IPX-RIP, without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports.

nwIpxRipOperationalTime.name: nwIpxRipOperationalTime
nwIpxRipOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxRipOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwIpxRipVersion.name: nwIpxRipVersion
nwIpxRipVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the IPX-RIP routing protocol firmware, in textual format.

nwIpxRipStackSize.name: nwIpxRipStackSize
nwIpxRipStackSize.description: Specifies the stack size of the IPX-RIP routing protocol thread. In order for a change of this value to take effect, the protocol (nwIpxRipAdminReset), IPX Routing Services (nwIpxSysAdminReset), or the device running Routing Services must be reset.

nwIpxRipThreadPriority.name: nwIpxRipThreadPriority
nwIpxRipThreadPriority.description: Specifies the run-time execution priority of the IPX-RIP routing protocol thread. In order for a change of this value to take effect, IPX-RIP (nwIpxRipAdminReset), IPX Routing Services (nwIpxAdminReset), or the device running Routing services must be reset.

nwIpxRipDatabaseThreshold.name: nwIpxRipDatabaseThreshold
nwIpxRipDatabaseThreshold.description: Specifies the run-time maximum number of IPX-RIP entries that can be held in the IPX-RIP route table.

nwIpxRipAgeOut.name: nwIpxRipAgeOut
nwIpxRipAgeOut.description: Specifies the amount of time, in seconds, that an inactive route table entry remains in the IPX-RIP route table before it is aged-out.

nwIpxRipHoldDown.name: nwIpxRipHoldDown
nwIpxRipHoldDown.description: Specifies the amount of time, in seconds, to wait before removing an entry from the route table, after receiving an update indicating that the destination has become unreachable. All routers exchanging IPX-RIP information must have the same hold down time. The time must be long enough to allow all participating routers to receive the same update.

nwIpxRipCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxRipCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxRipCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate system-wide IPX-RIP packet and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active on all router ports. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxRipCtrReset.name: nwIpxRipCtrReset
nwIpxRipCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate system-wide IPX-RIP protocol packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the IPX-RIP aggregate counters to 0. nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxRipCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxRipCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxRipCtrInPkts
nwIpxRipCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxRipCtrOutPkts
nwIpxRipCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxRipCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxRipCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during` nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxRipCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxRipCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxRipCtrInBytes
nwIpxRipCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxRipCtrOutBytes
nwIpxRipCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxRipCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxRipCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxRipCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxRipCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxRipCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxRipIfTable.name: nwIpxRipIfTable
nwIpxRipIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. Each entry can contain different values, allowing the routing protocol configuration to vary from router port to router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxRipIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which each entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfEntry.name: nwIpxRipIfEntry
nwIpxRipIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the IPX-RIP configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfIndex.name: nwIpxRipIfIndex
nwIpxRipIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfAdminStatus.name: nwIpxRipIfAdminStatus
nwIpxRipIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX-RIP routing protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes IPX-RIP to become active on the router port. Disabled (2) causes RIP to become inactive.

nwIpxRipIfOperStatus.name: nwIpxRipIfOperStatus
nwIpxRipIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the IPX-RIP routing protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwIpxRipIfOperStatus indicates any problem with your IPX-RIP configuration on the router port. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwIpxRipIfAdminStatus, IPX-RIP is not operating on the router port because of an invalid configuration.

nwIpxRipIfOperationalTime.name: nwIpxRipIfOperationalTime
nwIpxRipIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxRipIfOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwIpxRipIfVersion.name: nwIpxRipIfVersion
nwIpxRipIfVersion.description: Indicates the revision level of the IPX-RIP routing protocol in textual format.

nwIpxRipIfAdvertisement.name: nwIpxRipIfAdvertisement
nwIpxRipIfAdvertisement.description: Sets the interval, in seconds, at which IPX-RIP advertises its route table on the router port for which the entry exists. Change this value to cause IPX-RIP to advertise its route table more or less frequently.

nwIpxRipIfFloodDelay.name: nwIpxRipIfFloodDelay
nwIpxRipIfFloodDelay.description: Specifies the length of time, in seconds, that the IPX-RIP routing protocol will wait after discovering that a directly connected route has gone down, before flooding updates (triggered updates) on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 specifies that if a directly connected route goes down, updates will be sent immediately.

nwIpxRipIfRequestDelay.name: nwIpxRipIfRequestDelay
nwIpxRipIfRequestDelay.description: Specifies the length of time, in seconds, that the IPX-RIP routing protocol will wait after receiving a route request packet before sending a response on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 specifies that if a route request packet is received on the port, a response will be sent immediately.

nwIpxRipIfPriority.name: nwIpxRipIfPriority
nwIpxRipIfPriority.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxRipIfHelloTimer.name: nwIpxRipIfHelloTimer
nwIpxRipIfHelloTimer.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxRipIfSplitHorizon.name: nwIpxRipIfSplitHorizon
nwIpxRipIfSplitHorizon.description: Controls the operation of Split Horizon on the router port for which the entry exists. When Split Horizon is enabled, IPX-RIP keeps track of which router port route information is received on, and prevents information about a route from being sent back out the same router port it was received on.

nwIpxRipIfPoisonReverse.name: nwIpxRipIfPoisonReverse
nwIpxRipIfPoisonReverse.description: Controls the operation of Poison Reverse on the router port for which the entry exists. When Poison Reverse is enabled, IPX-RIP advertises any downed route as unreachable during the period of time that it must wait (nwIpxRipHoldDown) before removing the route from the route table.

nwIpxRipIfSnooping.name: nwIpxRipIfSnooping
nwIpxRipIfSnooping.description: Controls the operation of IPX-RIP Snooping on the router port. When RIP Snooping is enabled the IPX-RIP routing protocol operates in passive mode, so that it receives route information, builds and maintains a route table, but does not advertise or send updates on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfType.name: nwIpxRipIfType
nwIpxRipIfType.description: Indicates whether the directly connected network segment does or does not support broadcast media access. If broadcast media access is supported, IPX-RIP advertisements are sent out one broadcast packet per router port. If broadcast media access is not supported, IPX-RIP advertisements are sent to each neighbor directly.

nwIpxRipIfXmitCost.name: nwIpxRipIfXmitCost
nwIpxRipIfXmitCost.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the common MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxRipIfAclIdentifier.name: nwIpxRipIfAclIdentifier
nwIpxRipIfAclIdentifier.description: Specifies the Access Control ID of the access control list in effect for IPX-RIP routing protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 indicates that there is no access control list in effect for IPX-RIP routing protocol packets on the router port.

nwIpxRipIfAclStatus.name: nwIpxRipIfAclStatus
nwIpxRipIfAclStatus.description: Controls the operation of the access control list identified by nwIpxRipIfAclIdentifier. Enabled (3) applies the access control list to all IPX-RIP routing protocol packet traffic on the router port for which the entry exists. Disabled (2) prevents the access control list from being applied.

nwIpxRipIfCtrTable.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrTable
nwIpxRipIfCtrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port.This table is indexed by nwIpxRipIfCtrIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB2 ifindex, which indentifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrEntry.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrEntry
nwIpxRipIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates the current packet and byte count of IPX-RIP routing protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrIfIndex
nwIpxRipIfCtrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxRipIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the per-port IPX-RIP packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxRipIfCtrReset.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrReset
nwIpxRipIfCtrReset.description: Resets the per-port IPX-RIP packet and byte counters on the router port for which this entry exists. Reset (2) resets the counters to 0. nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpRipIfCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxRipIfCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrInPkts
nwIpxRipIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been received, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrOutPkts
nwIpxRipIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrInBytes
nwIpxRipIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been received, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrOutBytes
nwIpxRipIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxRipIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwIpxRipIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxRipIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX-RIP routing protocol packets that have been discarded, during nwIpRipIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRouteTable.name: nwIpxRipRouteTable
nwIpxRipRouteTable.description: This table contains the IPX-RIP route table. This table contains an entry for each route learned through the IPX-RIP routing protocol. Only the best routes from this table are added to the IPX forwarding table to be used for packet switching.

nwIpxRipRouteEntry.name: nwIpxRipRouteEntry
nwIpxRipRouteEntry.description: Each entry describes the IPX-RIP route to the destination network for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRtNetId.name: nwIpxRipRtNetId
nwIpxRipRtNetId.description: This is the primary index into the IPX-RIP route table. This number indicates the Novell Network Number of the destination for which the entry exists. The IpxAddress consists of a network number of 4 octets

nwIpxRipRtIfIndex.name: nwIpxRipRtIfIndex
nwIpxRipRtIfIndex.description: This is a secondary index into the IPX-RIP route table. This number corresponds to the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRtSrcNode.name: nwIpxRipRtSrcNode
nwIpxRipRtSrcNode.description: This is a secondary index into the RIP route table. This number indicates the MAC-layer address of the source router from which this route was learned. A value of 0.0.0.0.0.0 indicates that the source is on the network segment directly connected to the router port, nwIpxRipRtIfIndex.

nwIpxRipRtHops.name: nwIpxRipRtHops
nwIpxRipRtHops.description: Indicates the number of hops required to reach the destination for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRtTicks.name: nwIpxRipRtTicks
nwIpxRipRtTicks.description: Indicates the amount of time (number of Time Ticks) required to reach the destination for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRtAge.name: nwIpxRipRtAge
nwIpxRipRtAge.description: Indicates the amount of time, in seconds, since an update has been received for the route for which the entry exists.

nwIpxRipRtType.name: nwIpxRipRtType
nwIpxRipRtType.description: Indicates whether the destination network is directly connected through the router port specified by nwIpxRipRtIndex, or is indirectly connected through another router, specified by nwIpxRipRtSrcNode.

nwIpxRipRtFlags.name: nwIpxRipRtFlags
nwIpxRipRtFlags.description: Specifies properties of the IPX-RIP route. The bit mask is as follows: source-changed (1), best source (2), local-net (4), net-down (8), update-fib-only (16).

nwIpxSapAdminStatus.name: nwIpxSapAdminStatus
nwIpxSapAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SAP protocol system-wide. Enabled (3) causes SAP to become active on all router ports configured and enabled for IPX routing services. Disabled (2) causes the protocol to become inactive.

nwIpxSapOperStatus.name: nwIpxSapOperStatus
nwIpxSapOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the SAP protocol system-wide. The value of nwIpxSapOperStatus indicates any problem with your SAP configuration. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwIpxSAPAdminStatus, the SAP protocol is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwIpxSapAdminReset.name: nwIpxSapAdminReset
nwIpxSapAdminReset.description: Resets the SAP protocol. Reset (2) forces a system-wide restart of SAP, without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports.

nwIpxSapOperationalTime.name: nwIpxSapOperationalTime
nwIpxSapOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxSapOperStatus, has been in its current state.

nwIpxSapVersion.name: nwIpxSapVersion
nwIpxSapVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the SAP protocol firmware, in textual format.

nwIpxSapStackSize.name: nwIpxSapStackSize
nwIpxSapStackSize.description: Specifies the stack size of the SAP protocol thread. In order for a change to this value to take effect, the protocol (nwIpxSapAdminReset), IPX Routing Services (nwIpxSysAdminReset), or the device running Routing Services must be reset.

nwIpxSapThreadPriority.name: nwIpxSapThreadPriority
nwIpxSapThreadPriority.description: Specifies the run-time execution priority of the SAP protocol thread. In order for a change to this value to take effect, SAP (nwIpxSapAdminReset), IPX Routing Services (nwIpxAdminReset), or the device running Routing Services must be reset.

nwIpxSapDatabaseThreshold.name: nwIpxSapDatabaseThreshold
nwIpxSapDatabaseThreshold.description: Specifies the run-time maximum number of entries that can be held in the SAP server table.

nwIpxSapAgeOut.name: nwIpxSapAgeOut
nwIpxSapAgeOut.description: Specifies the amount of time, in seconds, that an inactive server table entry remains in the SAP server table before it is aged out.

nwIpxSapHoldDown.name: nwIpxSapHoldDown
nwIpxSapHoldDown.description: Specifies the amount of time, in seconds, to wait before removing an entry from the SAP server table, after receiving an update indicating that the destination has become unreachable. All routers exchanging SAP information must have the same hold down time. The time must be long enough to allow all participating routers to receive the same update.

nwIpxSapCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxSapCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxSapCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (system-wide) SAP protocol packet and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active on all router ports. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxSapCtrReset.name: nwIpxSapCtrReset
nwIpxSapCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate (system-wide) SAP protocol packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the SAP aggregate counters to 0. nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxSapCtrAdminStatus, has been in the current state.

nwIpxSapCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxSapCtrInPkts
nwIpxSapCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxSapCtrOutPkts
nwIpxSapCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxSapCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxSapCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxSapCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxSapCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxSapCtrInBytes
nwIpxSapCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxSapCtrOutBytes
nwIpxSapCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxSapCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxSapCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxSapCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxSapCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been discarded system-wide, during nwIpxSapCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxSapIfTable.name: nwIpxSapIfTable
nwIpxSapIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. Each entry can contain different values, allowing the SAP configuration to vary from router port to router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxSapIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which each entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfEntry.name: nwIpxSapIfEntry
nwIpxSapIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the SAP configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfIndex.name: nwIpxSapIfIndex
nwIpxSapIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfAdminStatus.name: nwIpxSapIfAdminStatus
nwIpxSapIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SAP protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes SAP to become active on the router port. Disabled (2) causes SAP to become inactive.

nwIpxSapIfOperStatus.name: nwIpxSapIfOperStatus
nwIpxSapIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the SAP protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwIpxSapIfOperStatus indicates any problem with your SAP configuration on the router port. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwIpxSapIfAdminStatus. SAP is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwIpxSapIfOperationalTime.name: nwIpxSapIfOperationalTime
nwIpxSapIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxSapIfOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwIpxSapIfVersion.name: nwIpxSapIfVersion
nwIpxSapIfVersion.description: Indicates the revision level of the SAP protocol in textual format.

nwIpxSapIfAdvertisement.name: nwIpxSapIfAdvertisement
nwIpxSapIfAdvertisement.description: Sets the interval, in seconds, at which SAP advertises its server table on the router port for which the entry exists. Change this value to cause SAP to advertise its server table more or less frequently.

nwIpxSapIfFloodDelay.name: nwIpxSapIfFloodDelay
nwIpxSapIfFloodDelay.description: Specifies the length of time, in seconds, that the SAP protocol will wait after discovering that a directly connected route has gone down, before flooding updates (triggered updates) on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 specifies that if a directly connected route goes down, updates should be sent immediately .

nwIpxSapIfRequestDelay.name: nwIpxSapIfRequestDelay
nwIpxSapIfRequestDelay.description: Specifies the length of time, in seconds, that the SAP protocol will wait after receiving a server request packet, before sending a response on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 specifies that if a server request packet is received on the port, a response will be sent immediately.

nwIpxSapIfPriority.name: nwIpxSapIfPriority
nwIpxSapIfPriority.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxSapIfHelloTimer.name: nwIpxSapIfHelloTimer
nwIpxSapIfHelloTimer.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxSapIfSplitHorizon.name: nwIpxSapIfSplitHorizon
nwIpxSapIfSplitHorizon.description: Controls the operation of Split Horizon on the router port for which the entry exists. When Split Horizon is enabled, SAP keeps track of which router port information is received on, and prevents information about a server from being sent back out the same router port it was received on.

nwIpxSapIfPoisonReverse.name: nwIpxSapIfPoisonReverse
nwIpxSapIfPoisonReverse.description: Controls the operation of Poison Reverse on the router port for which the entry exists. When Poison Reverse is enabled, SAP advertises any downed server as unreachable during the period of time that it must wait (nwIpxSapIfHoldDown) before removing the server from the server table.

nwIpxSapIfSnooping.name: nwIpxSapIfSnooping
nwIpxSapIfSnooping.description: Controls the operation of SAP Snooping on the router port. When SAP Snooping is enabled SAP operates in passive mode, so it receives service information, builds and maintains a server table, but does not advertise or send updates on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) turns on SAP Snooping. Disabled (2) turns off SAP Snooping.

nwIpxSapIfType.name: nwIpxSapIfType
nwIpxSapIfType.description: Indicates whether the directly connected network segment does or does not support broadcast media access. If broadcast media access is supported, SAP advertisements are sent out, one broadcast packet per router port. If broadcast media access is not supported, SAP advertisements are sent to each neighbor router directly.

nwIpxSapIfXmitCost.name: nwIpxSapIfXmitCost
nwIpxSapIfXmitCost.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwIpxSapIfAclIdentifier.name: nwIpxSapIfAclIdentifier
nwIpxSapIfAclIdentifier.description: Specifies the Access Control List ID of the access control list in effect for SAP protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 indicates that there is no access control list in effect for SAP protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfAclStatus.name: nwIpxSapIfAclStatus
nwIpxSapIfAclStatus.description: Controls the operation of the access control list identified by nwIpxSapIfAclIdentifier. Enabled (3) causes the access control list to be applied to all SAP protocol packet traffic on the router port for which the entry exists. Disabled (2) prevents the access control list from being applied.

nwIpxSapIfCtrTable.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrTable
nwIpxSapIfCtrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxSapIfCtrIfIndex which indicates the value of MIB2 ifindex, which indentifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrEntry.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrEntry
nwIpxSapIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates the current packet and byte count of SAP protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrIfIndex
nwIpxSapIfCtrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of the MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxSapIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the per-port SAP packet and byte counters on the router port for which this entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxSapIfCtrReset.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrReset
nwIpxSapIfCtrReset.description: Resets the per-port SAP packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Reset (2) resets the counters to 0. nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxSapIfCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxSapIfCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrInPkts
nwIpxSapIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP protocol packets that have been received, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrOutPkts
nwIpxSapIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SAP packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrInBytes
nwIpxSapIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been received, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrOutBytes
nwIpxSapIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been transmitted, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxSapIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxSapIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the SAP packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxSapIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfTable.name: nwIpxSapServerIfTable
nwIpxSapServerIfTable.description: The table contains the SAP server table. This table contains an entry for each service learned of through the SAP protocol.

nwIpxSapServerIfEntry.name: nwIpxSapServerIfEntry
nwIpxSapServerIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the SAP route information for the Novell server and router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfNetId.name: nwIpxSapServerIfNetId
nwIpxSapServerIfNetId.description: This is the primary index into the SAP server table. This number corresponds to the Novell Network Number of the server offering the service. The network number consists of 4 octets.

nwIpxSapServerIfNode.name: nwIpxSapServerIfNode
nwIpxSapServerIfNode.description: This is a secondary index into the SAP Server Table. This is the MAC-layer address represented as an octetstring of the service offering the server for which the entry exists, represented as an octet string.

nwIpxSapServerIfSocket.name: nwIpxSapServerIfSocket
nwIpxSapServerIfSocket.description: This is a secondary index into the SAP Server Table. This is the socket number of the server application for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfServiceType.name: nwIpxSapServerIfServiceType
nwIpxSapServerIfServiceType.description: This is a secondary index into the SAP Server Table. This is the service type of the server application for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfIfNum.name: nwIpxSapServerIfIfNum
nwIpxSapServerIfIfNum.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port through which the service for which the entry exits is available.

nwIpxSapServerIfSrcNode.name: nwIpxSapServerIfSrcNode
nwIpxSapServerIfSrcNode.description: This is the MAC-layer address of the neighbor router from which the service was learned about.

nwIpxSapServerIfName.name: nwIpxSapServerIfName
nwIpxSapServerIfName.description: This is the name of the server offering the service for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfHops.name: nwIpxSapServerIfHops
nwIpxSapServerIfHops.description: Indicates the number of hops required to reach the server offering the service for which the entry exists.

nwIpxSapServerIfAge.name: nwIpxSapServerIfAge
nwIpxSapServerIfAge.description: Indicates the amount of time since a SAP update was last received for the server and service for which the entry exits.

nwIpxSapServerIfType.name: nwIpxSapServerIfType
nwIpxSapServerIfType.description: Indicates whether the server is on a network that is directly connected through the router port for which the entry exists, or is indirectly connected through another router specified by the value of nwIpxSapServerIfSrcNode.

nwIpxSapServerIfFlags.name: nwIpxSapServerIfFlags
nwIpxSapServerIfFlags.description: Specifies properties of the SAP service for which the entry exist. The bit mask is as follows: source-changed (1), best-source (2), not used (4), net-down (8), not used (16).

nwIpxFibTable.name: nwIpxFibTable
nwIpxFibTable.description: This table contains an entry describing each route being used to forward IPX traffic to each destination Novell network and node.

nwIpxFibEntry.name: nwIpxFibEntry
nwIpxFibEntry.description: Each entry describes the route to the destination Novell network and node for which the entry exists.

nwIpxFibNetId.name: nwIpxFibNetId
nwIpxFibNetId.description: Specifies the Novell Network Number of the destination for which the entry exists. The IpxAddress consists of four octets

nwIpxFibHops.name: nwIpxFibHops
nwIpxFibHops.description: Indicates the number of hops required to reach the destination for which the entry exists. It is considered as metric 1.

nwIpxFibTimeTicks.name: nwIpxFibTimeTicks
nwIpxFibTimeTicks.description: Indicates the amount of time, indicated by the number of TimeTicks, required for a packet to reach the destination network for which the entry exists. It is considered as metric 2.

nwIpxFibNextHopIf.name: nwIpxFibNextHopIf
nwIpxFibNextHopIf.description: Indicates the router port through which the next hop node is available. Packets destined for the network specified by the value of nwIpxFibNetId will be forwarded on this port.

nwIpxFibNextHopNet.name: nwIpxFibNextHopNet
nwIpxFibNextHopNet.description: Indicates the Novell Network Number portion of the fully formed next hop IPX Address of the next hop node.

nwIpxFibNextHopNode.name: nwIpxFibNextHopNode
nwIpxFibNextHopNode.description: Indicates the node portion of the fully formed next hop IPX Address.

nwIpxFibRouteType.name: nwIpxFibRouteType
nwIpxFibRouteType.description: Indicates the status of the route. A value of 3 indicates that the destination is on the network segment that is directly connected to the router port identified by nwIpxFibNextHopIf. A value of 4 indicates that the destination is on an indirectly connected network segment, which is reachable through the next hop router indicated by the value of nwIpxFibNextHopNodeId. A value of 2 indicates that the route is invalid.

nwIpxAclValidEntries.name: nwIpxAclValidEntries
nwIpxAclValidEntries.description: Indicates the number of valid entries that exist in the access control list table.

nwIpxAclTable.name: nwIpxAclTable
nwIpxAclTable.description: This table contains the access control list information for IPX traffic. This table contains entries, each of which allows packet forwarding between source/destination pairs to be permitted or denied. The list is identified by the Access Control List ID. Each list may contain multiple entries ordered by sequence number. When a particular access control list is searched, it is searched in sequence number order and the first match found ends the search. If no match if found, access defaults to permitted.

nwIpxAclEntry.name: nwIpxAclEntry
nwIpxAclEntry.description: Each entry contains IPX source/destination access information.

nwIpxAclIdentifier.name: nwIpxAclIdentifier
nwIpxAclIdentifier.description: This is the primary (major) index into the IPX access control list table. This value identifies the access control list by a unique identifier (at least 1) arbitrarily assigned by the user. All entries that have the same value for nwIpxAclIdentifier belong to the same access control list.

nwIpxAclSequence.name: nwIpxAclSequence
nwIpxAclSequence.description: This is the secondary (minor) index into the IPX access control list table. This number corresponds to a sequence number used to order multiple entries within the same access control list.

nwIpxAclPermission.name: nwIpxAclPermission
nwIpxAclPermission.description: Specifies whether access is allowed or denied between the source and destination address pair. Note that source and destination are interchangeable when bi-directional control is selected. To remove an existing entry set nwIpxAclPermission to invalid (2). Invalid entries disappear after reboot.

nwIpxAclMatches.name: nwIpxAclMatches
nwIpxAclMatches.description: Indicates the number of matches on this entry that have resulted in the permit/deny access restriction being applied as part of the forwarding process.

nwIpxAclDestNetNum.name: nwIpxAclDestNetNum
nwIpxAclDestNetNum.description: Specifies the destination Novell Network Number used to compare for matches on the access control list. A 0 value is a wildcard which matches any Novell Network Number.

nwIpxAclDestNode.name: nwIpxAclDestNode
nwIpxAclDestNode.description: Specifies the MAC-layer address of the destination node (represented as an octet string), used to compare for matches on the access control list. A value 0 is a wildcard, which matches any node.

nwIpxAclDestSocket.name: nwIpxAclDestSocket
nwIpxAclDestSocket.description: Specifies the socket number of the destination socket used to compare for matches on the access control list. A 0 value is a wildcard matching any socket.

nwIpxAclSrcNetNum.name: nwIpxAclSrcNetNum
nwIpxAclSrcNetNum.description: Specifies the Novell Network Number of the source Novell Network used to compare for matches on the access control list. A 0 value is a wildcard matching any Novell Network Number.

nwIpxAclSrcNode.name: nwIpxAclSrcNode
nwIpxAclSrcNode.description: Specifies the MAC-layer address of the source node (represented as an octet string), used to compare for matches on the Access Control List. A 0 value is a wildcard matching any node.

nwIpxAclSrcSocket.name: nwIpxAclSrcSocket
nwIpxAclSrcSocket.description: Specifies the socket number of the source socket to compare for matches on the Access Control List. A 0 value is a wildcard matching any socket.

nwIpxNetBIOSAdminStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSAdminStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector, system-wide. Enabled (3) causes the NetBios Broadcast Redirector to become active on any router port configured and enabled for IPX Routing Services. Disabled (2) causes the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector to perform a graceful shut-down on any active IPX router port.

nwIpxNetBIOSOperStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSOperStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector, system-wide.

nwIpxNetBIOSAdminReset.name: nwIpxNetBIOSAdminReset
nwIpxNetBIOSAdminReset.description: Resets the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector, system-wide. Reset (2) forces a restart of the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector without a graceful shut-down on any active router port and without effecting any other router application.

nwIpxNetBIOSOperationalTime.name: nwIpxNetBIOSOperationalTime
nwIpxNetBIOSOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIpxNetBiosOperStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxNetBIOSVersion.name: nwIpxNetBIOSVersion
nwIpxNetBIOSVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector firmware, in textual format.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (system-wide) NetBIOS broadcast packet and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active on all router port. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrReset.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrReset
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate (system-wide) NetBIOS broadcast packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the NetBIOS broadcast aggregate counters to 0. nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundreds of a second, that the nwIpxNetBIOSCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS broadcast packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS broadcast packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS broadcast packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS broadcast packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwIpxNetBIOSCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfTable.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfTable
nwIpxNetBIOSIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. Each entry can contain different values, allowing the NetBIOS Broadcast Redirector configuration to vary from router port to router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxNetBIOSIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfEntry.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfEntry
nwIpxNetBIOSIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the IPX NetBIOS broadcasting configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfIndex.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfIndex
nwIpxNetBIOSIfIndex.description: Indicates the value in MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfAdminStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfAdminStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of IPX NetBIOS broadcasting on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes this router port to become active. Disabled (2) causes it to become inactive.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of IPX NetBIOS broadcasting on the IPX router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperationalTime.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperationalTime
nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that IPX NetBIOS broadcasting, nwIpxNetBIOSIfOperStatus, has been in its current state on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrTable.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrTable
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrTable.description: This table contains the IPX NetBIOS packet and byte counters for each router port on this device.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrEntry.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrEntry
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrEntry.description: This is the primary index into the NetBIOS Interface Counter Table. This number corresponds to the index into the MIB 2 Interface Table which describes the router port for which this entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrIfIndex
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrIfIndex.description: This is the primary index into the IPX NetBIOS Interface Counter Table. This number correspoonds to the index into the MIB 2 Interface Table which describes the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX NetBIOS packet and bytes counters on the IPX router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active on the configured NetBIOS router port. Disabled (2) causes thes counters to become inactive on the configured NetBIOS router port.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrReset.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrReset
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrReset.description: Resets the NetBIOS packet and bvyte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Reset (2) resets the interface-specific counters to 0. nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that the interface-specific NetBIOS packet and byte counters have been active on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS packets that have been recieved, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS packets that have been transmitted, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationallTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS packets that have been administratively filtered, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of NetBIOS packets that have been discarded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been recieved, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been transmitted, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been administratively filtered, that were recieved on the router port for which the entry exists during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the NetBIOS packets that have been discarded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxNetBIOSIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastAdminStatus.name: nwIpxBcastAdminStatus
nwIpxBcastAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of IPX Broadcast. Enabled (3) casuses IPX Broadcast to become active on any configured IPX router port. Disabled (2) causes IPX Broadcast to perform a graceful shutdown on any active IPX router ports.

nwIpxBcastOperStatus.name: nwIpxBcastOperStatus
nwIpxBcastOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the IPX Broadcast.

nwIpxBcastAdminReset.name: nwIpxBcastAdminReset
nwIpxBcastAdminReset.description: Resets the IPX Broadcast. Reset (2) will force a restart of the IPX Broadcast without a graceful shutdown on any active IPX router port, without effecting any other router applications.

nwIpxBcastOperationalTime.name: nwIpxBcastOperationalTime
nwIpxBcastOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that IPX Broadcast has been in its current operational state.

nwIpxBcastVersion.name: nwIpxBcastVersion
nwIpxBcastVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of IPX Broadcast.

nwIpxBcastCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxBcastCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxBcastCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (device-wide) Broadcast packet and byte counters. enable (3) causes these counters to become active on any router port running Broadcast. disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive on all router port running Broadcast.

nwIpxBcastCtrReset.name: nwIpxBcastCtrReset
nwIpxBcastCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate (device-wide) IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the IPX Broadcast aggregate counters to 0. nwIpxBcasstCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that the aggregate (device-wide) IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters have been in the current administrative state.

nwIpxBcastCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxBcastCtrInPkts
nwIpxBcastCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been received, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxBcastCtrOutPkts
nwIpxBcastCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been transmitted, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been administaratively filtered, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been discarded, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxBcastCtrInBytes
nwIpxBcastCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been recieved, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxBcastCtrOutBytes
nwIpxBcastCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been transmitted, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxBcastCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX Broadcast packets that have been administratively filtered, device-wide, during nwIpxBcastOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxBcastCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the Broadcast packets that have been discarded, during nwIpxBcastCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfTable.name: nwIpxBcastIfTable
nwIpxBcastIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port configured for the IPX distance-vector based routing protocol. Each entry can contain different values, allowing the routing protocol configuration to vary from router port to router port. This table is indexed by nwIpxBcastIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfEntry.name: nwIpxBcastIfEntry
nwIpxBcastIfEntry.description: Specifies the IPX Broadcast configuration information for the logical IPX interface for which this entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfIndex.name: nwIpxBcastIfIndex
nwIpxBcastIfIndex.description: This index corresponds to the primary index into the MIB 2 Interface Table, which describes the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfAdminStatus.name: nwIpxBcastIfAdminStatus
nwIpxBcastIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX Broadcast on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (2) causes IPX Broadcast on this router port to become active. Disabled (2) causes IPX Broadcast to become inactive.

nwIpxBcastIfOperStatus.name: nwIpxBcastIfOperStatus
nwIpxBcastIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the IPX Broadcast on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfOperationalTime.name: nwIpxBcastIfOperationalTime
nwIpxBcastIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwIPXBcastIfOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrTable.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrTable
nwIpxBcastIfCtrTable.description: This table contains the IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters for each router port on this device.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrEntry.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrEntry
nwIpxBcastIfCtrEntry.description: This is the primary index into the Broadcast Interface Counter Table. This number corresponds to the index into the MIB 2 Interface Table which describes the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrIfIndex
nwIpxBcastIfCtrIfIndex.description: This is the primary index into the IPX Broadcast Interface Counter Table. This number corresponds to the index into the MIB 2 Interface Table which describes the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrAdminStatus
nwIpxBcastIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become acive on the configured IPX Broadcast router port. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive on the configured IPX Broadcast router port.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrReset.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrReset
nwIpxBcastIfCtrReset.description: Resets the IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Reset (2) resets the interface-specific counters to 0. nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime
nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that the interface-specific IPX Broadcast packet and byte counters have been in the current administrative state on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrInPkts.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrInPkts
nwIpxBcastIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been recieved, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutPkts
nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of Broadcast packets that have been transmitted, on the router port for which the entry existsl, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of IPX Broadcast packets that have been administratively filtered, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of Broadcast packets that have been dis- carded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrInBytes.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrInBytes
nwIpxBcastIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX Broadcast packets that have been recieved, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutBytes
nwIpxBcastIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX Broadcast packets that have been transmitted, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwIpxBcastIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX Broadcast packets that have been administratively filtered on the router port for which the entry exists during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwIpxBcastIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the IPX Broadcast packets that have been discarded on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwIpxBcastIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwIpxEchoAdminStatus.name: nwIpxEchoAdminStatus
nwIpxEchoAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the IPX Echo. Enabled (3) causes IPX ECHO to become active on any configured IPX router ports. Disabled (2) causes IPX Echo to perform a graceful shutdown on any active IPX router port.

nwIpxEchoOperStatus.name: nwIpxEchoOperStatus
nwIpxEchoOperStatus.description: Indicates the operating condition of IPX Echo.

nwIpxEchoAdminReset.name: nwIpxEchoAdminReset
nwIpxEchoAdminReset.description: Resets IPX Echo. Reset (2) will force a restart of IPX Echo without a graceful shutdown on any active IPX router port, without effecting any other router applications.

nwIpxEchoOperationalTime.name: nwIpxEchoOperationalTime
nwIpxEchoOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that IPX Echo has been in its current administrative state, nwIpxEchoOperStatus.

nwIpxEchoVersion.name: nwIpxEchoVersion
